<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/html4/loose.dtd"><html>

<head>
<title>SET-FRAME-DURATION</title>
</head>
<body>
	<h3><i>I set the frame-duration global variable to determine how often the 
	display is updated.</i> </h3>

	<font size="2" color="gray">Begin micro-behaviour</font>
	<p><b>SET-FRAME-DURATION </b></p>

	<font size="2" color="gray">Begin NetLogo code:</font>
	<pre>substitute-text-area-for tick-duration 1
set frame-duration tick-duration</pre>

	<font size="2" color="gray">End NetLogo code</font>
	<h2>Variants</h2>

	<p>The numbers can be replaced by any positive number. </p>

	<h2>How this works</h2>

	<p>It sets the global variables <i>frame-duration</i>.&nbsp; <i>

	frame-duration</i> controls how often the display is updated to reflect the 

	current state of the model. The system attempts to maintain a correspondence 
	between simulation time and real time only if the &quot;clocked&quot; switch in the 
	interface is on.</p>

	<h2>History</h2>



	<p>This was implemented by Ken Kahn. </p>

</body>

</html>
